Thanks @msjulesfit for making us this recipe one night. It’s now on our monthly rotation because it’s so easy, tasty and healthy! Lots of healthy fats and flavor. We have it with salad, rice, or sweet potatoes and veggies. It’s so versatile and makes great leftovers. 

1lb salmon 
1 1/2 tbsp lemon juice
1 1/4 tbsp olive oil
1 tbsp Dijon mustard 
3 + cloves minced garlic 
1 tbsp honey or maple syrup 
1/4 cup crushed pistachios 
Salt and pepper to taste 

Rinse and pat dry your salmon fillet. Cut slits on top to soak in the flavor. Line on parchment paper and heat oven to 375.

Mix the marinade ingredients together. Oil, lemon, Dijon, honey, and garlic. Pour over the salmon and add crushed pistachios on top. 

Bake for 17 minutes, remove and let rest for 5 minutes. Serve with your favorite sides. Enjoy! The best part is this is it’s pre-cleanse approved! 💚

Eating on vacation and 32 weeks pregnant! Not featured 2 mocktails at @florafarms and @acreresort! The mocktails available most places have really stepped it up. And thank goodness! 

I tried to get some workouts in this babymoon and I was so happy to have froze my green drink to get through TSA. It’s the most refreshing nutritional boost post-workout. For breakfast I had a smoothie almost everyday but mixed in this goat yogurt, fruit, chia and gluten free granola twice this trip to mix it up. It was so good I actually craved it! 

For lunch we ventured to my fave place @florafarms and split a farm salad with a delicious hot honey soppressata pizza. It was delish! I asked for a mocktail and they made me a watermelon basil julep. 

Dinner we finally tried @acreresort restaurant which was nice. We share the tuna tiradito which is a mix of tuna and toro. Most people don’t eat raw fish pregnant but if it’s high quality I think the nutritional benefits outweigh the risk. Tuna is safe under 6oz a week to avoid high mercury content, and we shared this dish. Cheddar biscuits were all the rave so we had to add those. The whipped honey butter complimented them well. For the main we shared the roasted organic chicken which was 10/10. And although we were stuffed they sent us a babymoon dessert that we couldn’t say no to. I don’t eat this naughty everyday, most days are a little more boring and routine but for vacation this day was a hit! Mix of health and indulgence.

🌷Cheers to a fabulous healthy weekend!

This smoothie is one of my favorite recipes to enjoy because it’s low sugar, high in fat, potassium and nutrients! Dates are known to help soften the cervix and help ease labor! Enjoy this smoothie anytime but especially if your nearing your due date like I am! I’m having this smoothie daily until delivery 💚 along with raspberry leaf tea day and night, spicy foods, my exercise ball daily, waking and listening to my body! 

Recipe
1 cup water or green drink 
1 small avocado (or half large) 
1 cup spinach or green kale 
5 small pitted dates (or 3-4 large) 
Pinch of cinnamon
1 tsp chia seeds
1 tbsp lemon juice
1 tbsp vanilla pea protein 
1 cup ice 

Blend well for 1-2 minutes until you have a solid creamy consistency. The dates take a while to blend well so they aren’t chunky. Enjoy!
